<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>出版物 |皮尤研究中心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/publications/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 13:25:36 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>71% 的美国房主表示他们的房屋保险费用上涨</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/06/71-of-u-s-homeowners-say-their-home-insurance-costs-have-gone-up/</link><description>房主最常提到的两个原因是保险公司想要赚更多钱以及维修和重建的成本。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 01:50:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/06/71-of-u-s-homeowners-say-their-home-insurance-costs-have-gone-up/</guid></item><item><title>许多美国人认为公用事业公司要为其不断上涨的家庭能源账单负责</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/06/many-americans-hold-utility-companies-responsible-for-their-rising-home-energy-bills/</link><description>四分之三的美国成年人表示，近年来他们的家庭能源成本有所上涨，其中 42% 的人表示这些成本上涨了很多。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 01:35:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/06/many-americans-hold-utility-companies-responsible-for-their-rising-home-energy-bills/</guid></item><item><title>问题措辞如何影响同性恋道德民意调查</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/decoded/2026/05/06/how-question-wording-affects-polling-on-the-morality-of-homosexuality/</link><description>一项新的调查实验显示，美国人基本上不区分“同性恋”和“同性恋行为”的道德，尽管某些亚群体可能会这样做。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 01:20:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/decoded/2026/05/06/how-question-wording-affects-polling-on-the-morality-of-homosexuality/</guid></item><item><title>约一半美国人继续表示特朗普政府在驱逐出境问题上做得“太多”</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/04/about-half-of-americans-continue-to-say-trump-administration-is-doing-too-much-on-deportations/</link><description>认为政府在驱逐非法居住的移民方面做得太少的比例略有上升，这主要是由共和党人推动的。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 01:46:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/04/about-half-of-americans-continue-to-say-trump-administration-is-doing-too-much-on-deportations/</guid></item><item><title>随着支持率下滑，特朗普在多项个人特质上失势</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2026/05/01/trump-loses-ground-on-several-personal-traits-as-approval-rating-slips/</link><description>大多数美国人（56%）表示，在特朗普任期内，联邦政府的道德和诚实整体水平有所下降。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 02 May 2026 01:29:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2026/05/01/trump-loses-ground-on-several-personal-traits-as-approval-rating-slips/</guid></item><item><title>美国人仍然批评特朗普政府对伊朗的态度</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/01/americans-remain-critical-of-trump-administrations-approach-to-iran/</link><description>62%的美国人不赞成特朗普对伊朗军事行动的处理方式，59%的人表示美国在使用武力方面做出了错误的决定。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 02 May 2026 01:14:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/01/americans-remain-critical-of-trump-administrations-approach-to-iran/</guid></item><item><title>大多数美国人现在表示美国外交政策忽视其他国家的利益</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/04/28/most-americans-now-say-u-s-foreign-policy-ignores-the-interests-of-other-countries/</link><description>对于美国是否为和平做出贡献、是否考虑别国利益、是否赢得世界尊重，各党派存在不同看法。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 01:51:24 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/04/28/most-americans-now-say-u-s-foreign-policy-ignores-the-interests-of-other-countries/</guid></item><item><title>关于美国枪支死亡的数据说明了什么</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/28/what-the-data-says-about-gun-deaths-in-the-us/</link><description>2024 年，美国枪支死亡人数连续第三年下降，但仍处于有记录以来最高的年度总数之列。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 01:36:24 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/28/what-the-data-says-about-gun-deaths-in-the-us/</guid></item><item><title>美国人对特朗普在乌克兰问题上的决策越来越没有信心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/04/23/americans-have-become-less-confident-in-trumps-decision-making-on-ukraine/</link><description>共和党和民主党对乌克兰战争仍然存在不同看法，尽管他们对俄罗斯和普京的看法总体上是负面的。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 01:25:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/04/23/americans-have-become-less-confident-in-trumps-decision-making-on-ukraine/</guid></item><item><title>天主教在许多国家因宗教信仰的转变而失去了人们，而新教则在一些国家获得了胜利。</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/23/catholicism-has-lost-people-to-religious-switching-in-many-countries-while-protestantism-has-gained-in-some/</link><description>在基督教内部，宗教转变对天主教和新教这两个最大的群体产生了不同的影响。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 01:10:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/23/catholicism-has-lost-people-to-religious-switching-in-many-countries-while-protestantism-has-gained-in-some/</guid></item></channel></rss>